<section id="sponsorship-guide" class="guide-section active">
<h2>Sponsor Family Members in Dubai: A Step-by-Step Guide</h2>
<div class="content-block">
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>Dubai is a hub for expatriates. Sponsoring family requires meeting legal steps, with eligibility and documentation requirements set by the UAE government.</p>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Eligibility</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>Salary:</strong> AED 4,000 or AED 3,000 + accommodation</li>
<li><strong>Employment Status:</strong> Employed / Business Owner</li>
<li><strong>Residency:</strong> Valid Residency Visa Required</li>
<li><strong>Relations:</strong> Spouse, Children, Parents, Stepchildren (NOC required)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Who Can Sponsor</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>Spouse:</strong> Men can sponsor wives; Women require AED 10,000 salary to sponsor husbands</li>
<li><strong>Children:</strong> Sons (up to 18–21 if studying), Unmarried daughters (no age limit)</li>
<li><strong>Parents:</strong> Prove sole support; AED 20,000 or AED 19,000 + accommodation</li>
<li><strong>Stepchildren:</strong> Need NOC and custody proof</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Required Documents</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Marriage Certificate (Required: Yes, Attested: Yes)</li>
<li>Birth Certificates (Required: Yes, Attested: Yes)</li>
<li>Employment Contract or Salary Certificate (Required: Yes)</li>
<li>Tenancy Contract (Required: Yes)</li>
<li>Medical Insurance (Required: Yes)</li>
<li>Medical Fitness Certificate (Required: Yes for 18+)</li>
<li>Passport Copies (Required: Yes)</li>
<li>Passport Photos (Required: Yes)</li>
<li>Emirates ID Application (Required: Yes)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Sponsorship Steps</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ol>
<li>Submit Residency Visa Application (via GDRFA or Typing Center)</li>
<li>Pay Visa Fees (AED 1,000–2,000 approx.)</li>
<li>Medical Fitness Test for 18+ family members</li>
<li>Apply for Emirates ID</li>
<li>Residency Visa Stamping at GDRFA</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Visa Validity</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>Duration:</strong> 1–3 Years (renew before expiry)</li>
<li><strong>Grace Period:</strong> 30 Days after expiry</li>
<li><strong>Switch to Work Visa:</strong> Possible upon employment</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="content-block">
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p>Follow the process carefully. Stay informed of policy changes and consult GDRFA when needed.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section id="vat-guide" class="guide-section">
<h2>VAT Registration in Dubai: A Comprehensive Guide</h2>
<div class="content-block">
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>VAT registration enables businesses to charge VAT, claim input tax, and comply with UAE tax laws.</p>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Why Register</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Legal Compliance</li>
<li>Input Tax Credit</li>
<li>Business Credibility</li>
<li>Avoid Penalties</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Who Must Register</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li><strong>Mandatory:</strong> Annual taxable turnover > AED 375,000</li>
<li><strong>Voluntary:</strong> Annual turnover > AED 187,500</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Required Documents</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Business Trade License</li>
<li>Passport Copy of Owner/Partners</li>
<li>Emirates ID Copy of Owner/Partners</li>
<li>MOA (Memorandum of Association)</li>
<li>Business Activity Details</li>
<li>Bank Account Details</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>VAT for Small Business</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Reclaim VAT on purchases</li>
<li>Improved reputation</li>
<li>Simplified accounting</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>VAT Registration Steps</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ol>
<li>Register online via FTA portal</li>
<li>Submit required documents</li>
<li>Receive VAT Number</li>
<li>Maintain records & file returns</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>VAT Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Document Assistance</li>
<li>Process Guidance</li>
<li>Post-Registration Support</li>
<li>Tailored Services for Small Business</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="content-block">
<h3>Conclusion</h3>
<p>VAT registration ensures tax compliance. Contact Amercenter for end-to-end VAT support.</p>
</div>
</section>

<section id="corporate-services-guide" class="guide-section">
<h2>Business & Corporate Services in Dubai</h2>
<div class="content-block">
<h3>Overview</h3>
<p>WTZ Documents Clearance Service offers comprehensive assistance for professionals and businesses with various needs in the UAE, particularly in Dubai.</p>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Business Corporate Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<ul>
<li>Tenancy contract registration</li>
<li>Ejari registration</li>
<li>Tawtheeq registration (for Abu Dhabi home agreements)</li>
<li>Visa renewal</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Business Centre Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Business centre services, including one-year Ejari with inspections if you’re renting a space facility, offer:</p>
<ul>
<li>Office space rental</li>
<li>Meeting rooms</li>
<li>Reception services</li>
<li>Mail handling</li>
<li>Virtual office services</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Typing Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Typing services may include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Document preparation</li>
<li>Data entry</li>
<li>Transcription services</li>
<li>Document editing</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>PRO Services (Public Relations Officer)</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>PRO services often provide:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business registration</li>
<li>License renewal</li>
<li>Document attestation</li>
<li>Government transactions</li>
<li>Tenancy Contracts Registering</li>
<li>Virtual office Ejari</li>
<li>Visa assistance typing application</li>
<li>Tawtheeq Abu Dhabi home agreement</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Amer Center and Tawasul Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>The Amer Center and Tawasul services are related to government services or business registration processes in the UAE, offering support for various official procedures.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Dubai Economic Department (DED) Services</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Dubai Economic Department (DED) services may include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business registration</li>
<li>License issuance</li>
<li>Trade name reservation</li>
<li>Business setup services</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>License Requirements and Service Structure</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>The type of license required depends on the business activity. Some common license types in Dubai include:</p>
<ul>
<li>Commercial license</li>
<li>Professional license</li>
<li>Industrial license</li>
</ul>
<p>The service structure and cost vary depending on the type of license, business activity, and other factors.</p>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Visa Requirements and Process</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Visa requirements and processes in the UAE typically involve:</p>
<ul>
<li>Sponsorship</li>
<li>Medical test</li>
<li>Emirates ID application</li>
<li>Typing and attestation of documents</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Tenancy Contract Ejari Review Process</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Ejari is a contract registration system in the UAE. The review process typically involves:</p>
<ul>
<li>Registering the tenancy contract</li>
<li>Verifying the contract details</li>
<li>Paying registration fees</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>License Requirements</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>License requirements in Dubai typically involve:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business plan</li>
<li>Memorandum of Association (MOA)</li>
<li>Articles of Association (AOA)</li>
<li>Proof of payment of fees</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Bank Account Opening</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>To open a bank account in the UAE, businesses typically need:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business license</li>
<li>Memorandum of Association (MOA)</li>
<li>Articles of Association (AOA)</li>
<li>Proof of address</li>
<li>Identification documents</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>License Types and Departments</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>The type of license required for approval varies depending on the department and business activity. Here's a general overview:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Dubai Economic Department (DED):</strong> Requires a license for businesses operating in mainland Dubai, covering activities like trading, manufacturing, and services.</li>
<li><strong>Free Zone Authority:</strong> Requires a license for businesses operating in designated free zones, offering benefits like 100% foreign ownership and tax exemptions.</li>
<li><strong>Dubai Health Authority (DHA):</strong> Requires a license for healthcare-related businesses, such as medical clinics, pharmacies, and healthcare services.</li>
<li><strong>Dubai Tourism Board:</strong> Requires a license for tourism-related businesses, such as hotels, tour operators, and travel agencies.</li>
<li><strong>Dubai Municipality:</strong> Requires a license for businesses related to food safety, environmental health, and construction.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Approval Process for Licenses</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>General steps for the approval process:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Determine the Relevant Department:</strong> Identify the department responsible for issuing licenses for your business activity.</li>
<li><strong>Meet the Requirements:</strong> Ensure you meet the necessary requirements, such as business plan, premises, and documentation.</li>
<li><strong>Submit Application:</strong> Submit your application, along with required documents and fees.</li>
<li><strong>Review and Approval:</strong> The department reviews your application and may request additional information or clarification.</li>
<li><strong>License Issuance:</strong> Upon approval, the license is issued, and you can commence business operations.</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Documents Required for License</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Documents typically required:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business Plan: Outlining your business activities, goals, and financial projections.</li>
<li>Memorandum of Association (MOA): Defining the company's structure and purpose.</li>
<li>Articles of Association (AOA): Outlining the company's internal management and governance.</li>
<li>Proof of Premises: Evidence of office or business premises.</li>
<li>Identification Documents: Passports, Emirates ID, and other identification documents for owners and shareholders.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="accordion">
<div class="accordion-header"><h3>Steps for Obtaining a License</h3><span class="arrow">▼</span></div>
<div class="accordion-content">
<p>Here's a structured outline of categories and steps for obtaining a license in Dubai:</p>
<h4>I. License Categories</h4>
<ul>
<li>Commercial License: For trading, retail, or wholesale activities.</li>
<li>Professional License: For professional services, such as consulting, medical, or educational services.</li>
<li>Industrial License: For manufacturing or industrial activities.</li>
<li>Tourism License: For tourism-related activities.</li>
</ul>
<h4>II. Steps for Obtaining a License</h4>
<ol>
<li><strong>Choose Business Activity and License Category:</strong> Determine the business activity and corresponding license category.</li>
<li><strong>Select Legal Structure:</strong> Choose a legal structure (e.g., Limited Liability Company (LLC), Free Zone Company, or Sole Proprietorship).</li>
<li><strong>Reserve Trade Name:</strong> Reserve a trade name with the relevant authority (e.g., Dubai Economic Department (DED) or Free Zone Authority).</li>
<li><strong>Prepare Documents:</strong> Prepare required documents (MOA, AOA, business plan, proof of payment of fees).</li>
<li><strong>Submit Application:</strong> Submit the license application to the relevant authority.</li>
<li><strong>Pay Fees:</strong> Pay the required fees (License fee, LSA fee, PRO service fee).</li>
<li><strong>Obtain License:</strong> Receive the business license after approval and payment of fees.</li>
</ol>
<h4>III. Additional Requirements</h4>
<ul>
<li>Office Space: Some license categories require a physical office space.</li>
<li>Visa Requirements: Depending on the business activity and structure, visas may be required for employees or owners.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="content-block">
<h3>Tips for Business Setup</h3>
<ul>
<li>Consult with Experts: Engage with business setup experts or consultants to ensure a smooth process.</li>
<li>Verify Requirements: Confirm the specific requirements for your business activity and department.</li>
<li>Plan Ahead: Allow sufficient time for the approval process, which can take several weeks or months.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</section>

